=left class=m><span class=title> AE PoF Idea</span><hr size=1> I must admit, I haven't ventured around Plane of Fear that much, but I had this idea of the PoF AE break-in and wanted to get your thoughts.  Would it work?  Do mobs resist to much?  Thoughts?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1st group</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
2 - warriors<br>
2 - clerics<br>
2 - enchanters(55+)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2nd and 3rd group</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1 - cleric<br>
1 - enchanter<br>
4 - wizards(53+)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Giving us a grand total of: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> 18 people</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
2 - tanks<br>
4 - clerics<br>
4 - enchanters<br>
8 - wizards(53+)<br>
<br>
That's it. Just three groups. This is what I see happening:<br>
<br>
Group 1 does the break-in and runs to the west wall. If anything agro's they pull to the west wall and enchanters mez/stun. Then group 2 and 3 zone in and make the same run. Once everyone is together, the two warriors pull mobs to the west wall and enchanters mez/stun. Once we have a number we are happy with, then the enchanters AE stun, while the wizards AE PB nuke. Rince and repeat. <br>
<br>
I guess I was mostly thinking this group would take the lower part of this zone and not the whole zone.  Just a small group going in to have a little AE fun.  So, I'm open to your thoughts. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   thx!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelaurieldragonstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elauriel Dragonstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/01 4:48:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE PoF Idea</span><hr size=1> This is pretty much how my guild breaks Fear.  We stagger the entry of the three groups, then we all get to the west wall and AoE it up.  We don't have nearly as many wizards in our guild though, so it would be even more fun and easier for you guys<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><img src ="http://www.guildmagic.com/pics/32282.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=silvesti>Silvesti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/01 12:08:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE PoF Idea</span><hr size=1> Thx for the info Elauriel.  I was wondering if you had any resist problems, and what kind of issues you've ran up against.  I hope to try this out soon, so any problems you saw/had would be great to know about.  Also, How many enchanters/wizards did u go up with?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umalagis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malagis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/01 12:59:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE PoF Idea</span><hr size=1> Bear in mind I havent done this -<br>
<br>
That being said I believe strongly that 2 groups can do all of Fear except the mini-bosses. Heres the breakdown -<br>
<br>
2 Identical groups:<br>
1 55+ Bard<br>
1 55+ Enchanter<br>
1 56+ Cleric<br>
3 56+ Wizards <br>
<br>
Invis up and run to the ledge, letting the bards go first, with AE fear song goin full tilt (if you have 2 60 bards let em hit DA song as soon as they hit the ground then run as a group to the ledge, if not, stick to this)<br>
<br>
You must remember to stand as near as possible to on top of each other...<br>
<br>
When mobs arrive Bards twist AE slow/snare Cantana of Replenishment and a debuff song (if possible). i.e. both do Cantana one does ae slow/snare, other does resist debuff.<br>
<br>
Chanters just chain stun for all they are worth. You may want one to AE tash as second cast, while one just stuns.<br>
<br>
6 Wizards chain nuking Jylls should waste any roamers you get.<br>
<br>
If you do not seem to have much of a train, send one bard out with selos to round up some more. He can sing AE slow to help create a decent train (remember if the mobs are within melee range only 3 will stick to a single toon, others will forget you).<br>
<br>
Once dead, med up (c2 + cantana = fast med) and send the bard for more.<br>
<br>
Done properly I think Fear lasts about 1 hr before you hit minis. Temple will require the Clerics to pull, and you should all move over close so DA doesnt wear off, also have SoW potions or jboots for your clerics.<br>
<br>
At this point you may allow those useless Melees to come in so you can drop the mini-bosses :-)<br>
<br>
Malagis(x) Windrider<br>
AE Prophet of Gnomallah<br>
The Hand<br>
Xev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzzappbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zzapp Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/01 1:08:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE PoF Idea</span><hr size=1> We've done it on Brell with around 18-22 people, and it was a blast. <br>
<br>
Need at least 5 wizards 56+.<br>
Need at least 3-4 chanters (around 55+)<br>
<br>
Also need single pull elements in the raid.  When that HUGE fun train is all dead, almost all your wizards are OOM.  thats when you need tanks to block for you and keep those baddies off the medding casters.<br>
<br>
We cleared fear in about 2 hours once the pulls got started, and I'm sure that it was our personal record for clearing fear.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Zzapp &lt;Skyre Draneth&gt; of Brell<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelaurieldragonstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elauriel Dragonstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 10:00:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE PoF Idea</span><hr size=1> We had two level 60 enchanters, 2 55+ wizards,  a handful of druids and mages for additional AoE support, plus a few clerics, tanks etc.  I personally had no problems with resist in Fear, and I don't believe the enchanters did either.<br>
<br>
The main issue I found was that the puller would bring a few mobs in, but they seemed to have a hard time getting them to us all wrapped into a ball for easier AoE.<br>
<br>
I think having at least one more wizard and one more enchanter would have made it much smoother and less mana intensive. <p><img src ="http://www.guildmagic.com/pics/32282.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uborim69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>borim 69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/2/01 8:14:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PoFAE</span><hr size=1> Well I was not in on the break in but it took awhile and when groups 3and 5 got up there that is when we did AE's we cleared most of fear in about 3 hours. We had 6 wizards only 3 of them were 54+ and 4 enchanters. I have to tell you I never had so much fun in my life. Most of the tanks were whining how they could not target the mob because they had so many casters in the way,&lt;hehe&gt;.<br>
                   Zebbidiah Rahl 51 lvl wizard<br>
